Comment: (Usually called BUN) - This would be the POC instrument

Long Common Name: Alkaline phosphatase [Enzymatic activity/volume] in Serum or Plasma
Alanine aminotransferase [Enzymatic activity/volume] in Serum or Plasma
Aspartate aminotransferase [Enzymatic activity/volume] in Serum or Plasma

Comment: This is the  the code included in the CBC auto.  It is NOT obtained via the automated counting but uses a chemistry method just like most other hemoglobins

Long Common Name: Hematocrit [Volume Fraction] of Blood by Automated count
Comment: Most Hematocrits delivered by referral and hospital laboratories will be produced by automated count- and will be delivered with this code

Long Common Name: Platelets [#/volume] in Blood by Automated count
Comment: 99% of all blood count will be automated so this is usually the right choice

Long Common Name: C reactive protein [Mass/volume] in Serum or Plasma
Comment: Low sensitivity CRP is used to assess severity of inflammatory diseases such as rheumatoid arthritis.

Long Common Name: Vitamin D+Metabolites [Mass/volume] in Serum or Plasma

Comment: Note there is also a biologically intact PTH which identifies more of the polypeptide. The intact and biologically intact PTH are important for confirming removal of parathyroid tumor. Note other more specific LOINC  codes exist that define value of PTH post surgery

Long Common Name: Cyclic citrullinated peptide IgG Ab [Units/volume] in Serum
Chlamydia trachomatis DNA [Presence] in Unspecified specimen by Probe & target amplification method
Short Name: C trach DNA XXX Ql PCR

Long Common Name: Erythrocyte mean corpuscular hemoglobin [Entitic mass] by Automated count
Erythrocyte mean corpuscular hemoglobin concentration [Mass/volume] by Automated count
